   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1865_08_12_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_B_Telge_Shanghai_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>⟨1865<lb/>Shanghai 12/8 <lb/>B. Telge<lb/>W. R[eceived] 15th Aug⟩</p>
         <pb facs="1865_08_12_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_B_Telge_Shanghai_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <p>B. TELGE<lb/>By means of “Kienlein” Shanghai 12 Aug 1865 <lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler +
                Co.<lb/>Nagasaki<lb/>I came into possession, at the time, of your esteemed
                <lb/>letter from 24th of last month and thank you kindly for <lb/>sending a sample
                of the rifles stored at yours for Mr. <lb/>J. C. Möller.<lb/>The demand for rifles +
                ammunitions has dropped<lb/>here again somewhat recently, but I hope <lb/>to be able
                to sell the above-mentioned rifle very soon <lb/>+ will then notify you. <lb/>What
                you said about the caplock rifles of Messrs. Schabert + <lb/>Möller, I take note of
                + with drawing your attention <lb/>to the enclosed letter sign <lb/>p.p. B.
                Telge<lb/>Joh Nölting</p>
         <pb facs="1865_08_12_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_B_Telge_Shanghai_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <pb facs="1865_08_12_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_B_Telge_Shanghai_4.tif" n="4"/>
      </body>
   </text>
